					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12050459#post-4279871</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12050459/scp-4154#post-4279871</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 13 Jun 2019 18:29:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>aismallard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4598089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The concept is fine, but the execution doesn't really do it for me. While I understand that there's horror to be found in &quot;mundane thing is actually very anomalous and disturbing&quot;, this article doesn't do enough to <em>show</em> me. Something like an interaction log where a regular and mnesticized individual, where you sell the reader on the dissonance by contrasting their reactions to the scip.</p> <p>Novote.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show&nbsp;nitpicks</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;nitpicks</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Class-C mnestic</p> </blockquote> <p>This is not a thing. Mnestics go from W to Z, with Class-Ws being weak but acceptable for continual usage, and Class-Zs giving you perfect immunity to antimemes, but having the downside of causing you to have a seizure and die.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
